1. 飲茶  
廣東話：我哋每星期六朝早都約好去茶樓飲茶，食吓蝦餃、叉燒包同埋蛋撻～  
English: We always make plans to go to yum cha at the morning dim sum service every Saturday.

2. 圖書館  
廣東話：呢度新開咗間圖書館，環境好安靜，仲有空調，真係適合溫書！  
English: A new library’s opened here—it’s super quiet and air-conditioned, perfect for studying!

3. 養聲  
廣東話：佢下個月要開個人演唱會，所以成個月都在養聲，連話都少講，連冷氣房都唔敢出。  
English: He’s got a solo concert next month, so he’s been taking care of his voice for a whole month—even talking less and dare not step out of the air-conditioned room.

4. 票尾  
廣東話：買完機票記得收好票尾，日後退票或者改期都要用到呢張紙。  
English: Don’t forget to keep the ticket stub after buying your flight ticket—you’ll need it for refunds or rescheduling later.

5. hacker  
廣東話：呢間公司上個月被 hacker 攻擊，客戶資料差啲就外洩晒。  
English: This company got hacked last month, and customer data nearly got leaked.

6. 石斛蘭  
廣東話：呢盆石斛蘭好特別，佢唔係種喺土入面，而係攀喺塊枯木上面生長，真係有啲仙氣。  
English: This Dendrobium orchid is special—it doesn’t grow in soil but clings onto a dead log, giving it quite an ethereal vibe.

7. 吊詭  
廣東話：呢個理論聽落好吊詭：講人越努力，命運越會阻住佢成功……  
English: This theory sounds absurd: the harder you work, the more fate seems to block your success…

8. 吊詭  
廣東話：佢話自己唔鍾意出風頭，但每次聚會都穿得最靚，真係好吊詭。  
English: He claims he doesn’t like the spotlight, yet at every gathering he’s dressed the most flashy—totally contradictory!

9. 各為其主  
廣東話：雖然佢哋喺公司入面成日爭拗，但其實係各為其主，各自要完成老闆交俾佢哋嘅任務。  
English: Although they’re always arguing at work, it’s because they’re each serving their own master—trying to fulfill the tasks assigned by their respective bosses.

10. 軨蓋  
廣東話：部車個軨蓋壞咗，開車時風好大，耳仔都震到麻麻晒。  
English: The car’s steering wheel cover’s broken—when driving, the wind’s so strong it’s making my ears numb.

11. 打哥夫  
廣東話：阿明成日打哥夫，上個禮拜仲打贏咗區際錦標賽，真係好叻！  
English: Ming plays golf all the time—and last week he even won the district championship; he’s really good!

12. 免揀  
廣東話：呢間快閃店係免揀貨，所有衫都係預先配好尺碼同款式，買完即場拎走。  
English: This pop-up store sells “no-selection” items—all clothes are pre-packed in specific sizes and styles, so you just buy and go.

13. 擺闊佬  
廣東話：佢請人食飯，一餐就點咗三萬蚊嘅龍蝦同魚翅，真係擺闊佬到極！  
English: He treated people to dinner and ordered dishes worth 30,000—lobsters and shark fin! He’s showing off his wealth to the extreme.

14. 廣播劇  
廣東話：我小學時成日收聽廣播劇，《紅樓夢》入面林黛玉嘅聲音，至今都記得。  
English: When I was in primary school, I used to listen to radio dramas—still remember the voice of Lin Daiyu in *Dream of the Red Chamber*.

15. 錄影機  
廣東話：阿婆成日話：「我哋以前用部錄影機，一集《上海灘》都要等一星期先播完。」  
English: Grandma always says: “Back in the day, with our VCR, we had to wait a whole week for each episode of *The Shanghai Bund*.”

16. 吟詩吟唔甩  
廣東話：警察將監控片段同證人供詞一齊出示，個疑犯即刻啞口無言，真係吟詩吟唔甩！  
English: When the police showed the surveillance footage and witness statements together, the suspect was left speechless—there’s no way to deny it!

17. 佈道大會  
廣東話：呢個禮拜六有個大型佈道大會，好多教友都預早幾星期預留時間去參與。  
English: There’s a big evangelism meeting this Saturday—many churchgoers booked time weeks ahead to attend.

18. 寫手  
廣東話：呢間出版社專門請寫手幫名人代筆出書，連序言都係寫手捉刀寫嘅。  
English: This publishing house hires ghostwriters to pen books for celebrities—even the preface’s written by the writer.

19. 寫手  
廣東話：呢個網紅好叻，佢自己唔識打字，但成日請寫手幫佢寫貼文，一貼就爆紅。  
English: This influencer’s really skilled—even though he can’t type well, he always hires ghostwriters to draft his posts, and every one goes viral.

20. 代打  
廣東話：佢話自己唔係唔想打比賽，而係要代打—因為佢個弟弟先係正選，但佢病咗，所以要佢頂上。  
English: He says he’s not unwilling to play—he’s just stepping in as a substitute, because his younger brother’s the main player but got sick, so he had to fill in.

21. 茶碗  
廣東話：呢個茶碗係日本陶藝大師手製，表面有冰裂紋，握落去暖暖的，好有禪意。  
English: This teacup is handcrafted by a Japanese ceramic master—its cracked-glaze pattern feels warm to hold, full of Zen vibes.

22. 茶隔  
廣東話：泡鐵觀音時，我會將茶葉放進茶隔，再拎起茶隔倒進公道杯，咁樣茶湯就唔會有渣。  
English: When brewing Tieguanyin, I put the tea leaves in a strainer, lift it out, and pour the tea into a fairness pitcher—so the brew stays clear with no residue.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈  
廣東話：老闆成日遲到，但見到員工遲一分鐘就扣薪，真係只許州官放火，唔准百姓點燈！  
English: The boss is always late, yet deducts salary if staff are even one minute late—total double standard!

24. 獨唱  
廣東話：今晚演唱會最後一曲係獨唱，佢一開口，全場都安靜落來，連呼吸都放輕。  
English: The final song of tonight’s concert is a solo—when he starts singing, the whole audience falls silent, even holding their breath.

25. 快人快事  
廣東話：佢話做就係，唔講廢話，即刻叫人送合同過嚟，真係快人快事！  
English: He says “just do it,” no nonsense—immediately asks someone to send over the contract. What a straightforward, decisive move!

26. 四腳獸  
廣東話：公廁外面貼咗張告示：「禁止偷拍四腳獸」，原來係防有人偷拍廁所入面嘅私密畫面。  
English: The public toilet’s got a sign: “No偷拍四腳獸 (no偷拍 of four-limbed beasts)—apparently to stop people secretly filming intimate moments inside.

27. 無米粥  
廣東話：佢哋成日話「等我哋煲陣無米粥先」，但幾年過咗都冇下文，原來只係拖時間嘅口號。  
English: They always say, “Let’s first ‘boil congee without rice’ (start preliminary talks),” but years passed with no follow-up—it was just a stalling tactic.

28. 義會  
廣東話：以前鄉下人想開小店，就靠義會集資，大家每月攞幾蚊，輪到自己就拎走一筆，再慢慢還。  
